{"name": "obr", "metadata": {"name": "obr", "version": "1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 1 - Planning", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: Public Domain", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": null, "license": "Public Domain", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "deferred exception handling", "upload_time": 1734189707}, "documentation": ["**NAME**\n\n`obr` - deferred exception handling\n\n**SYNOPSIS**\n\n```\n>>> from obr.object import *\n>>> o = Object()\n>>> o.a = \"b\"\n>>> str(loads(dumps(o)))\n\"{'a': 'b'}\"\n```\n\n**DESCRIPTION**\n\n`obr` contains all the python3 code to program objects in a functional\nway. It provides a base Object class that has only dunder methods, all\nmethods are factored out into functions with the objects as the first\nargument. It is called Object Programming (OP), OOP without the\noriented.\n\n`obr` allows for easy json save//load to/from disk of objects. It\nprovides an \"clean namespace\" Object class that only has dunder\nmethods, so the namespace is not cluttered with method names. This\nmakes storing and reading to/from json possible.\n\n**INSTALL**\n\n```\n$ pipx install obr\n$ pipx ensurepath\n```\n\n**SOURCE**\n\nsource is at <https://github.com/bthate/obr>\n\n**AUTHOR**\n\nBart Thate \\<<mailto:bthate@dds.nl>>\n\n**COPYRIGHT**\n\n`obr` is Public Domain.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "obr.mods.face", "documentation": ["This file is placed in the Public Domain.", "pylint: disable=W0611,E0402", "ruff: noqa: F401"], "functions": [{"name": "obr.mods.face.__dir__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "obr.mods.log", "documentation": ["This file is placed in the Public Domain.", "pylint: disable=C,R,W0105,E0402"], "functions": [{"name": "obr.mods.log.log", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "event", "type": null, "